On a related note, I hear Bush Jr. may, or may not, have jerked off to a Victoria's Secret catalogue last week. We'll have to convene a special comission for inquiry, and make double damn certain he didn't wipe himself using an official White House hand towel.<br>
<br>
We can't have this kind of moral decline in our leadership. Or is it that we can't allow partisan battles to obstruct the flow of government in the most powerful country in the world?<br>
<br>
Can never keep those straight. Damn liars, can't stand 'em. Makes you wonder why the founding fathers didn't make it so only priests could be elected president.<br>
<br>
Oh wait, now I remember. <br>
<br>
BECAUSE THAT WOULD BE FUCKING STUPID.<br>
<br>
Because in a country where most people are so infantile that they believe the president should serve as a personal father figure, lying to people is a good idea if you want to keep your job. Because in a nation where the business of government can be halted in order to interrogate a president over a cumstain, lying is an even better idea if you want to keep your job. Because whether a sitting president is boffing an intern, a goat, or the entire cast of the Mormon Tabernacle boys choir, is none of your fucking business. And if self-righteous, self-appointed moral inquisitors didn't make it their business, maybe we'd have a snowball's chance in hell of electing someone who wasn't a professional liar. <br>
<br>
Possibly the only two honest men in office during the 1900s were TDR and Truman. Neither were elected, they were both VPs when the sitting president died. It is doubtful that either one of them would have won had they run for office.<br>
<br>
If two candidates stood for election, odds are you'd elect the liar and not the honest man. Because the liar tells you what you want to hear, rather than what you need to hear. Do that for a hundred years, and it's amazing what kind of filth will inhabit your presidency.<br>
<br>
I don't blame the Democrats. I don't blame the Republicans. I don't blame Bill, and I don't blame Ronald. I blame the ridiculous children who have demanded that the president behave like a Sunday school teacher whenever he's not running the most powerful country in history.<br>
<br>
We haven't had a sane, responsible president in decades for a reason...mostly because catering to the individual emotional, intellectual, spiritual, moral, ethical, political and legislative whims of over 225 million people is a waste of time.<br>
<br>
Honest people can't elected anymore. We've made damn sure of that.<br>
<br>
Now if you'll excuse me, I have to go subpoena the President's hand towels. I can't WAIT to find out which catalogue model gives him the best wood.<br>
