He is the man elected to provide executive decision-making for four to eight years. He is NOT the man elected to provide moral guidance.<br>
<br>
Conservative or liberal, I FULLY support a president who lies to a Congress which oversteps its authority. It may not be the resistance I'd like to see, but it beats the hell out of seeing a presidency, ANY PRESIDENCY, subjected to Congressional inquisition at the whim of party machinations.<br>
<br>
The buck stops at the president's office. Not Congress, not your house, and not mine. Harassment of a sitting president for anything less than an absolutely capital transgression is, in my opinion, unacceptable. As long as we continue to do it, we'll get nothing but liars and yesmen in the position.<br>
<br>
I'll take the liar over the yesman any day of the week and twice on Sunday, and it hasn't got a goddamn thing to do with the economy. It has do with being the goddamn president, rather than a Congressional whipping boy.<br>
<br>
If it's not clicking for you, look up 'checks and balances' in a history book.<br>
